                    <abstract lang="eng">We introduce the concept of a cloud-antichain, which is a natural generalization of antichains in partially ordered sets, and solve some seemingly basic extrenal problems for them. Following the discovery of our identity (in[1]) we found the ‘missing term’, which converts Bollobás&apos; inequality into an identity. It immediately yields the uniqueness in the Sperner Theorem for unrelated chains of subsets, which are an example of a cloud-antichain.</abstract>
